      <prompt>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <div>A 23-year-old African man who underwent total thyroidectomy 3 years ago presents with an unsightly swelling over the scar of the surgery. He complains of needle-like pains and itching over the swelling.</div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <div>A 35-year-old woman underwent a total thyroidectomy. On the fourth post-operative day she complains of tingling and numbness in the face and fingers.</div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <div>A 65-year-old man presents to his GP with a history of lethargy and weight gain. He underwent total thyroidectomy 6 months ago for thyroid carcinoma.</div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <div>A 35-year-old man who underwent lobectomy of the thyroid gland is found to have a weak hoarse voice a few days after surgery.</div>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </prompt>
